1.237
log
@TheRegister.co.uk: Microsoft Anti-UNIX campaign backfires
@
text
@a33 17
<h2>April, 2002</h2>
<li><font color=#009000><strong>
<a href="http://www.theregister.co.uk/content/53/24681.html">
Microsoft's anti-Unix campaign backfires</a>,
The Register, April 3, 2002
</strong></font><br />
What do UniSys and Microsoft use when they want to set up a secure site?
According to this article,
the site <i>wehavethewayout.com</i> -
a joint Unisys/Microsoft site designed to lure people from UNIX to MS-Windows -
was originally set up with OpenBSD running Apache, and hurriedly
switched to MS-Windows and IIS once this fact was made public.
When we tried it day of the article, the site gave a 404 on its default page.
Better than showing CIOs defenestrating themselves, I suppose.
Better than an April Fools' joke, in fact.
</p>

